d to create a basic structure for `solution.py` that includes the necessary components for real-time collaboration, data input, tracking, analysis, report generation, and visualization.\n\nHere is a basic implementation of `solution.py` that can serve as a starting point:\n\n```python\n# solution.py\n\nimport threading\nimport time\nfrom collections import defaultdict\nimport matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n\nclass SportGame_Collaborative_Analytics:\n    def __init__(self):\n        self.data = defaultdict(list)\n        self.lock = threading.Lock()\n\n    def add_data(self, analyst_id, metric, value):\n        with self.lock:\n            self.data[metric].append((analyst_id, value, time.time()))\n\n    def get_data(self, metric):\n        with self.lock:\n            return self.data[metric]\n\n    def generate_report(self):\n        report = {}\n        for metric, entries in self.data.items():\n            report[metric] = [(analyst_id, value, time.strftime(\'%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S\', time.localtime(timestamp))) for analyst_id, value, timestamp in entries]\n        return report\n\n    def visualize_data(self, metric):\n        with self.lock:\n            analyst_ids, values, timestamps = zip(*self.data[metric])\n        plt.figure(figsize=(10, 5))\n        plt.plot(timestamps, values, marker=\'o\')\n        plt.title(f\'Data Visualization for {metric}\')\n        plt.xlabel(\'Time\')\n        plt.ylabel(\'Value\')\n        plt.xticks(rotation=45)\n        plt.tight_layout()\n        plt.show()\n\n# Example usage\nif __name__ == "__main__":\n    analytics = SportGame_Collaborative_Analytics()\n    analytics.add_data(\'Analyst1\', \'Speed\', 25)\n    analytics.add_data(\'Analyst2\', \'Speed\', 27)\n    print(analytics.generate_report())\n    analytics.visualize_data(\'Speed\')\n```\n\nThis code provides a basic structure for the `SportGame_Collaborative_Analytics` application, including methods for adding data, retrieving data, generating reports, and visualizing data. It 